description:
The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the JPX-Nikkei 400 Net Total Return Index.
 The index is designed to track the performance of equity securities of issuers who are primarily listed on the JASDAQ Stock Exchange or the following sections of the Tokyo Stock Exchange: the first section (for large companies), the second section (for middle-sized companies) and the "Mothers" (for high-growth and emerging stocks). The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the underlying index.
